---
---
<section class="pt-32 pb-20 md:pt-40 md:pb-28">
  <div class="container text-center">
    <div class="badge mb-8">
      <span>🐻</span>
      Built by a Berkeley student, for Berkeley students
    </div>

    <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black text-text-primary leading-[1.05] tracking-tight mb-8">
      Your Cal study buddy,<br/>
      <span class="text-cal-gold">in the terminal.</span>
    </h1>

    <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-text-secondary max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12 leading-relaxed">
      OpenMind connects to bCourses, reads your lectures, tracks your deadlines, and talks like a Bear. Any LLM. Runs on your machine. Your data stays local.
    </p>

    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-3 mb-20">
      <button id="copy-btn" class="btn-primary flex items-center gap-2.5 text-base px-7 py-3"
        onclick="navigator.clipboard.writeText('pip install openmind')">
        <code class="font-mono font-medium">pip install openmind</code>
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 opacity-40" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 16H6a2 2 0 01-2-2V6a2 2 0 012-2h8a2 2 0 012 2v2m-6 12h8a2 2 0 002-2v-8a2 2 0 00-2-2h-8a2 2 0 00-2 2v8a2 2 0 002 2z"/>
        </svg>
      </button>
      <a href="https://github.com/qazybekb/openmind" target="_blank" class="btn-secondary text-base px-7 py-3">
        View on GitHub →
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- Hero terminal — large and prominent -->
    <div class="terminal max-w-3xl mx-auto text-left shadow-2xl shadow-black/40">
      <div class="terminal-header">
        <div class="terminal-dot bg-[#ff5f57]"></div>
        <div class="terminal-dot bg-[#febc2e]"></div>
        <div class="terminal-dot bg-[#28c840]"></div>
        <span class="ml-3 text-xs text-text-muted font-sans">openmind</span>
      </div>
      <div class="terminal-body text-text-secondary text-[13px] md:text-sm">
        <div class="mb-3">
          <span class="text-text-muted">$</span> <span class="text-text-primary">openmind</span>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-5 text-text-secondary">
          🐻 Hey Oski! Go Bears! 💙💛
        </div>
        <div class="mb-4">
          <span class="text-text-muted">You →</span> <span class="text-text-primary">What's due this week?</span>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-2 mb-5">
          <div>🔥 <span class="text-text-primary font-medium">HIGH</span> — NLP midterm report <span class="text-text-muted">(due Fri, 30% of grade)</span></div>
          <div>📋 <span class="text-text-primary font-medium">MED</span>&ensp; — Social Issues writing prompt <span class="text-text-muted">(due Mon)</span></div>
          <div>📚 <span class="text-text-primary font-medium">LOW</span>&ensp; — Finance case reading <span class="text-text-muted">(due next Wed)</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="text-text-muted">
          I'd start with the NLP report — that's 30% of your grade and due in 3 days.<br/>
          You could knock out the outline at a Moffitt table tonight.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  document.getElementById('copy-btn')?.addEventListener('click', function() {
    const btn = this;
    const original = btn.innerHTML;
    btn.innerHTML = '<code class="font-mono font-medium">Copied!</code> ✓';
    setTimeout(() => { btn.innerHTML = original; }, 1500);
  });
</script>
